    11| * Security:
    12| * - NEVER returns a secret value. Present values are masked (first 3 + last 2,
    13| *   short values fully masked) so the owner can confirm WHICH value is set
    14| *   without exposing it.
    15| * - Verification probes return pass/fail + HTTP status only, never the value.
    16| *
    17| * Honesty:
    18| * - `knownInRork` is derived from the project's declared Rork env panel so the
    19| *   "present in Rork but not injected into this runtime" case is reported
    20| *   exactly (`PRESENT_IN_RORK_NOT_INJECTED`) instead of a generic "missing".
